   <indicator ascending="1" measure="5">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Methodology for Damage and Loss Assessment and Analysis of Environmental Needs designed and implemented.</narrative>
    </title>
    <baseline iso-date="2018-07-10" value="Methodology for Damage and Loss Assessment and Analysis of Environmental Needs not designed." year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN"></narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2018-07-10"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-07-10"></period-end>
     <target value="Methodology for Damage and Loss Assessment and Analysis of Environmental Needs designed by the MADS and implemented by 5 RegionalEnvironmental Authorities (CARs)."></target>
     <actual value="Milestone 1. Preliminary document with the scope and content of the methodology for damage and loss assessment and analysis ofenvironmental needs for mainland ecosystems. Progress of 10%, as set for 2019. A document was prepared, which includesjustification, scope, objectives, conceptual framework and preliminary structure for the EDANA development.Milestone 2. Designand validation of the EDANA through four workshops. Progress as proposed for 2019 (20%). Four workshops were held; one with expertsin the field of damage assessment and post-disaster environmental needs analysis, and the other three with three CARs (CORNARE, CVSand CAR), in order to socialize progress and obtain key information as input for adjusting the EDANA&apos;s methodologicaldesign.Milestone 3. Implementation of the methodology by five pilot CARs. Progress of 14% compared to the 70% set for 2019. Theadvances in the EDANA methodology were implemented by the Cundinamarca Regional Environmental Authority (CAR), for a forest"></actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
  <result aggregation-status="0" type="1">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intermediate Results Indicator</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="1" measure="5">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">National Technical Assistance (TA) Program in DRM and Climate Change Adaptation (CCA), designed, approved and implemented</narrative>
    </title>
    <baseline iso-date="2018-07-10" value="National TA Program in DRM and CC not designed." year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN"></narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2018-07-10"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-07-10"></period-end>
     <target value="National TA Program in DRM and CCA, designed, approved and implemented in 5 departments and 2 sectors."></target>
     <actual value="Milestone 1. Proposed preliminary structure of the National TA Program (definition of objective and scope). Progress as expectedfor 2019 (10%). This progress corresponds to the preparation of a preliminary proposal by the UNGRD, based on an initial structuredrafted by the MVCT. This proposal includes scope, baseline, conceptual framework, prioritization criteria, strategic topic areasand methodology. Milestone 2. Design of the National TA Program. No progress made thus far."></actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
  <result aggregation-status="0" type="1">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intermediate Results Indicator</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="1" measure="5">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRM instruments for inter-institutional coordination of the National DRM system, designed and approved</narrative>
    </title>
    <baseline iso-date="2018-07-10" value="Programmatic Component of the National DRM Plan out of date; National Emergency Response Strategy with response protocols outdated;Strategy of Resilient Recovery to Disaster and Climate Change (CC)not designed." year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN"></narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2018-07-10"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-07-10"></period-end>
     <target value="Three risk management instruments for inter-institutional coordination of the National Disaster Risk Management System (SNGRD),designed and approved:1.	Programmatic component of the National DRM Plan (PNGRD) updated.2.	Five response protocols in theframework of the National Emergency Response Strategy updated.3.	Strategy of Resilient Recovery to Disaster and CC designed."></target>
     <actual value="Instrument: Programmatic Component of the National DRM Plan (PNGRD) Updated (100%).Milestone 1. Document with the initialproposal to update the PNGRD programmatic component. Work has been carried out with 20 sectors, for which the critical points ofthe programmatic component to be adjusted have been identified. This has resulted in the identification of 585 projects of theprogrammatic component that require update in terms of targets, contents and deadlines.Instrument: National Emergency ResponseStrategy with response protocols updated (100%)Milestone 1. Design of 5 response protocols (hurricanes, volcanoes, floods,earthquakes and landslides). Progress as expected for 2019 (33.4%). Components in which progress has been made include: TemporaryShelters, Emergency Humanitarian Aid, Search and Rescue, Water and Sanitation, and Critical Incident Management."></actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
